author: Muhd Fadzil
text:
Absolutely love this gym! From the moment I walked in, the staff made me feel welcome and supported. The equipment is modern, clean, and well-maintained, and there's a great variety for both cardio and strength training.

Sha and Jose are knowledgeable, friendly, and genuinely invested in helping you reach your goals. I especially appreciate how motivating the environment is whether you're a beginner or experienced, you'll feel right at home.

text:
Very cool and chill gym,

but have to highlight one thing , due to close proximity to the heavy weights, this wall may suffer from damages, due to gym goer whom may accidentally collide their free heavy weights into it, if they are not careful.

author: Nur Nadia
text: Staff here are nice & friendly and the gym is new & clean :-) Equipment all new, aircon is strong too! Even though it's small, you can still have a decent workout here if you plan your exercises properly. I think the staff planned the layout well since they had space constraints. Pretty neat for a neighbourhood gym. Highly recommended for people staying in the area!!

author: Blaine
text:
A very small neighbourhood gym. While the existing equipment are in impeccable condition, given the space constraints, this gym is lacking a lot of important equipment, especially for training back. Still, it can be a viable gym for those who live around the neighbourhood.

However, huge props to Jonathan, a staff member who was cordial and friendly to my friends and I when we were there. I can tell that he was actively getting feedback to improve the gym, which is commendable.

author: Khairul Azhar Sharifuddeen
text:
> Small (but larger than neighbourhood gym)
> Multiple racks and cable areas
> Cardio area available
> Machine equipment available
> 1 bus stop from woodlands mrt

> Toilets and shower availability
> ecstatically okay

author: Hafiz
text:
Edit: No more smell in my last visit

Had to edit my review as the gym occasionally reeks of urine, especially today. It's really bad at the treadmill area. Is anyone else noticing this or am I tripping?

text: For such a small space it‚Äôs very well equipped with a range of different equipments & weights. There are also toilets (with bidets üòÇüëèüèªüëèüèª) & shower facilities. The best part is that it is not too crowded even during peak periods. Unlike other gyms in busier areas, I‚Äôve never had to share the equipments or rack with more than 1 person at most. Would definitely recommend if you live in the area!

author: Jonathan
text:
Friendly and welcoming staff, compact gym with mostly everything you need for a workout, showers/toilets are a great plus as well.

Would recommend coming before 9pm as there's usually a crowd.

Heard news that the staff are also bringing in more equipment, great to see that our feedback is actually heard.

For example, the gym can consider having a lat pull down machine that allows multiple back exercises to be performed which provides much more exercises than solely a leg machine taking up much space
